</DOCHDR>
<html>
<head>
<title>Duplantier: ORGANIZED CRIME -- 2/26/96</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">

<BLOCKQUOTE><BLOCKQUOTE><a href="/townhall/columnists/"><img align="right" vspace="10" src="/townhall/columnists/thcolm.gif"></a>
<b>BEHIND THE HEADLINES</b><BR>


<i>
Commentary from America's Future, Inc.<br>

<a href="/townhall/columnists/duplbio.html">F.R. Duplantier</a><br>
February 26, 1996<br><p></i>
<h2>Organized Crime</h2>


<i><blockquote>
"The face of organized crime in America is dramatically changing. " 
The challenge is to defend ourselves against it without giving up the 
freedoms we hold dear.

</blockquote></i>

<P>
"In the 1980s, the government began cracking down on organized 
crime," reports Robert McGarvey in the February issue of the American 
Legion magazine. The results were nothing short of spectacular. 
"Nowadays, the chiefs of the American Mafia . . . are languishing in 
prison, leaving the organizations they left behind in disarray." Their 
sudden departure created an equal employment opportunity for other 
minority gangsters, however, and "literally dozens of ethnic crime 
groups have emerged to fill the void." McGarvey reports that 
"Colombian drug barons earn billions of dollars annually in the United 
States. Japanese gangsters . . . claim a mounting presence in Hawaii, 
along with scattered outposts on the West Coast. Various Mexican 
criminals . . . wreak havoc in U.S. border states."

<BR> 
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
Most menacing of all are the Triad gang of Hong Kong and the so-called 
Russian Mafia. "The Triads' business is heroin," says McGarvey. "Some 
60 percent of the drugs entering the United States are traced to Triad 
sources, primarily Burmese poppy fields that have long been controlled 
by Chinese criminals." The Triads have not neglected to diversify, 
however. Their other interests, according to McGarvey, include 
"extortion, prostitution, international car theft, and their much-
publicized involvement in alien smuggling," the latter netting them more 
than $3 billion a year. McGarvey warns that "the Triads are building 
alliances with U.S. street gangs," whose teenaged members "represent a 
sizable, often coldblooded army that will take on even the most vicious 
jobs."

<BR> 
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
The Russian Mafia, composed of former KGB officers and various gulag 
graduates, "now ranks as one of law enforcement's top priorities," says 
McGarvey. A deputy assistant FBI director recently told Congress that 
the Russian Mafia may soon be "the principal organized crime group in 
the United States." He warns that its members are extremely violent and 
have already linked up with Italian and Colombian comrades in crime. 
The FBI's New York bureau chief reports that he has "transferred agents 
and other scarce resources out of traditional organized crime 
investigations and foreign counterintelligence to concentrate on Russian 
crime."

<BR> 
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
McGarvey asserts that "America's new Russian gangsters also rank as 
perhaps the nation's most versatile criminals." He says that "the most 
fearsome aspect of the Russian Mafia is its access to the ill-guarded 
military warehouses of the old USSR. This makes the 'Moscow mob' 
instant leaders on the international arms black market, where they sell 
everything from automatic weapons to rocket launchers. Russian thugs 
even are alleged to be dealing in weapons-grade radioactive materiel."

<BR> 
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
McGarvey worries that "U.S. law enforcement currently is ill-equipped 
to battle groups like the Triads and the Russian Mafia." We should be 
concerned about the damage to our society from "corruption, violence, 
and wholesale theft," but we should never sacrifice our democratic 
freedoms in the fight against internal enemies.


<P><P>

<i>
Behind The Headlines is produced by America's Future, a nonprofit 
educational organization dedicated to the preservation of our free-
enterprise system and our constitutional form of government. For a free 
transcript of this broadcast, send a self-addressed, stamped envelope to: 
America's Future, 7800 Bonhomme, St. Louis, Missouri 63105
</i>

</blockquote></blockquote>




