<HTML>
<TITLE> The Washington Watch : Let Freedom Ring!</TITLE>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/townhall/FRC/wash.gif" WIDTH=425
HEIGHT=125>
<H2> Let Freedom Ring!</H2>

<P>
</CENTER>
<HR SIZE = 3 WIDTH = 50%><P>
<P>
What should every schoolchild know about the history of this land of liberty we call America?  The National History Standards Project, sponsored by the National Endowment for the Humanities and the U.S. Education Department, attempted to provide an answer to this
question; however, their report, released in late 1994, contains serious omissions and amusing political correctness.  In response, the Family Research Council prepared <I> Let Freedom Ring!, </I>an outline of U.S. history that avoids political fashion and emphasizes real knowledge of America's past.

<P>

&#169 1995 Persimmon IT, Inc. </HTML>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT15-B33-332</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA033-000677-B041-107</DOCOLDNO>
