   <H1>Christopher Flannery</H1>

</CENTER>

<p>
<a href="mailto:CFlannery@MSMAIL.APU.EDU">Christopher Flannery</a> is Professor of Political Science, Azusa Pacific University, Azusa, 
California.  He holds the M.A. and Ph.D. in Government from the Claremont Graduate School.  
He has served as a member of the California Department of Education Review Team for 
Draft National Standards for Civics and Government, and as a consultant to the 
California Department of Education with respect to civics education and textbook 
assessment.  

<p>
Dr. Flannery has published articles in academic periodicals including <i>The Journal of 
Contemporary Studies</i>, T<i>he Claremont Review of Books</i>, <i>Grand Strategy: Countercurrents</i> and 
<i>The Western Political Quarterly</i>.  

