<H1>Brian Kennedy</H1>

</CENTER>

<p>

<a href="mailto:britrav@aol.com">Brian Kennedy</a> is Vice President of the <b>Claremont Institute</B> and Director of
	the <b>Golden State Center for Policy Studies</B> in Sacramento.  He is a graduate
	of Claremont McKenna College with degrees in Political Science and History.

<P>

	Mr. Kennedy is a political scientist whose expertise includes California
	public policy, and foreign policy issues.  He serves also as contributing
	editor to <I>National Review West</I>, the western edition of William F. Buckley
	Jr.'s  <I>National Review</I>.  He is the author most recently of an article on
	welfare reform in Los Angeles.  

<P>

	He can be reached at the Golden State Center, (916) 446-7924 
	or at <a href="mailto:britrav@aol.com">britrav@aol.com</a>.

