   <H1>Nazalee Topalian</H1>

</CENTER>

<a href="mailto:topalian@msn.com">Nazalee Topalian</a> is Director of Communcations at the Claremont Institute. Before joining the the Institute in 1996, she was Finance Program Director at GOPAC in Washington, D.C. Previously, she has worked as a research assistant in the International Communications department at the Center for Strategic and International Studies, and also at the International Foundation for Electoral Systems, where she was an observer for the Eastern European Election's Conference in Budapest, Hungary.
<p>
She received her B.A. in political philosophy and communications from Ashland University in Ohio and studied with the University of Michigan's Graduate Sovieet Studies Program in Armenia.
<P>
She has taught classes on development and marketing, and is active in the veteran community.
